synopsis:
  Don't drop cost centres around variables of type `IO ()`
description:
  The logic to drop cost centres (and other ticks) around variables of non-function
  type has been updated to be more conservative: it now only drops ticks when
  the variable's type is definitely not a function type, even after looking
  through newtypes or reducing type families. This ensures we don't erroneously
  drop valid cost centres (which loses valuable profiling information).
